<white>synopsys:</>
    the command <green>grep</> is used to filter the output of another
    command in the sense that only lines that are matching a substring
    pattern are returned.
    
    the grep command is intended to be used via a pipe.
    
<white>usage: </><light_gray>$command</> | <green>grep</> <cyan>$pattern</>

<white>arguments:</>
    <light_gray>$command</> - although command is not an argument of the grep
               command, it is here for illustrating purposes.
    
    <green>grep</>     - the <green>grep</> command
    
    <cyan>$pattern</> - a string pattern.

<white>remarks:</>
    
    The grep command is case sensitive, meaning that "foo" is not equal with "Foo"

<white>examples:</>
    ls | <green>grep</> <cyan>"root"</>
    ls | <green>grep</> <cyan>"Category"</>
